 {"id":"franken_numpy-xtfk","title":"numpy.kaiser python wrapper parity","description":"Add fnp_python.kaiser passthrough wrapper around numpy.kaiser(M, beta). Returns the M-point Kaiser window with shape parameter beta. Include oracle test covering: M=11 with beta=0 (rectangular), beta=14 (typical), M=4 small window, M=1 returning [1.0], M=0 empty, dtype float64, symmetry across center, and beta=0 producing all-ones.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:07:43.604427794Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T10:49:33.920235167Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T10:49:33.918200171Z","close_reason":"Closed by cc-numpy — wrapper + oracle parity test delivered in commit 460e6e6 (verified via git log --grep br-franken_numpy-xtfk).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_numpy-xuzx","title":"numpy.linalg.matrix_norm python wrapper parity","description":"Add fnp_python.matrix_norm passthrough wrapper around numpy.linalg.matrix_norm(x, /, *, keepdims=False, ord='fro'). Returns the matrix norm. Include oracle test covering: ord='fro' (Frobenius) on 2-D, ord=1 (max column sum), ord=inf (max row sum), ord=-1, ord=-inf, ord=2 (largest singular value), ord=-2 (smallest singular value), batched 3-D input, and keepdims=True.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T12:07:35.263476123Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T10:41:12.827305623Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T10:41:12.825456519Z","close_reason":"Closed by cc-numpy — wrapper + oracle parity test delivered in commit 27c2154 (verified via git log --grep br-franken_numpy-xuzx).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
